          "parts": [
            {
              "content_type": "audio_transcription",
              "text": "All right, so my cat has got a cut on his foot that got infected. Took him to the vets. He's now been given like antibiotics and other medicine and painkillers and stuff. He's got a cone on his head to stop him from licking the cut on his foot, but he's kind of, he seems really like upset and he's not really eating. Is there anything we can do to help him eat or like there's the biggest issue, he's like, he's circling around, he's just walking around like the perimeter of the house, so he's not really, it's not, it's not something he normally does. He just keeps circling around the perimeter of the house. Is there anything you can suggest that we can do to help him?",
