            {
              "content_type": "audio_transcription",
              "text": "Poor little guy, it sounds like he’s going through a lot! First, on eating: you might tempt him with something especially appetising—like some warm, smelly food (maybe a bit of plain cooked chicken or fish) to encourage him. Keep offering small amounts regularly, and ensure he’s got water nearby, too.\n\nAs for the circling, it could be a reaction to discomfort or the disorientation from the cone. You can help by giving him a quiet, cosy space with fewer obstacles so he feels safer. If he’s still not eating or his behaviour gets more worrying, a follow-up call to the vet is wise. But a bit of patience, extra cuddles (if he’s in the mood), and some tasty offerings can often coax them back into routine.",
